# TEST CASES FOLDER STRUCTURE [MANDATORY]

## Rule: Test cases MUST use a two-folder layout under `Cursor-Project/test_cases/`

When creating, moving, or organizing test cases, ALWAYS follow this structure. This is the only accepted layout for test case files.

---

## Root layout (Backend/ and Frontend/ sub-folders)

**Path:** `Cursor-Project/test_cases/`

Test case files are split into **two sub-folders** by testing layer:

| Folder | Contents |
|--------|----------|
| **Backend/** | Backend (API) test cases — `TC-BE-N`. One `.md` file per topic. |
| **Frontend/** | Frontend (UI) test cases — `TC-FE-N`. One `.md` file per topic. |

Each topic produces **two files** with the **same `<Topic_name>`** — one in each folder:

**Path patterns:**
- `test_cases/Backend/<Topic_name>.md` — contains only **Backend Test Cases** (`TC-BE-N`).
- `test_cases/Frontend/<Topic_name>.md` — contains only **Frontend Test Cases** (`TC-FE-N`).

- **&lt;Topic_name&gt;** = descriptive name for the task, bug, feature, or flow being tested. Use underscores for multi-word names.
- The Backend file MUST NOT contain Frontend test cases, and vice versa.

**Examples:**
- `test_cases/Backend/Invoice_cancellation.md` + `test_cases/Frontend/Invoice_cancellation.md`
- `test_cases/Backend/Product_contract_create.md` + `test_cases/Frontend/Product_contract_create.md`
- `test_cases/Backend/Zero_amount_liability_receivable.md` + `test_cases/Frontend/Zero_amount_liability_receivable.md`

If a topic genuinely has no backend or no frontend test cases, the file in that folder MUST still be created with a note: *"No backend test cases applicable for this scope."* or *"No frontend test cases applicable for this scope."*

---

## READMEs (index files)

- **test_cases/README.md** — Root index listing all topics with links to both Backend and Frontend files.
- **test_cases/Backend/README.md** — Index of all backend test case files.
- **test_cases/Frontend/README.md** — Index of all frontend test case files.

Update all applicable READMEs whenever a new test case file is added.

---

## TC numbering

- **Backend:** `TC-BE-1`, `TC-BE-2`, `TC-BE-3`, …
- **Frontend:** `TC-FE-1`, `TC-FE-2`, `TC-FE-3`, …

Each TC heading includes its type: `TC-BE-1 (Positive): {title}` or `TC-FE-2 (Negative): {title}`.

## Mandatory coverage per file

- Each file (Backend and Frontend) MUST include at least one **(Positive)** and one **(Negative)** test case (when the section is applicable).
- If a topic has no applicable test cases for that layer, the file still exists with an N/A note (see above).

